<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 11 at 9:20PM CDT  by NWS Tulsa</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of northeastern Le Flore
County through 945 PM CDT...
At 919 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated strong thunderstorms 4 miles
southeast of Bokoshe and 2 miles north of Cameron. Movement was
northeast at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations in or near the path include...
Pocola...                         Spiro...
Panama...                         Cameron...
Shady Point...                    Rock Island...
Scullyville...                    Braden...
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 1100 PM CDT for west central
Arkansas...and southeastern Oklahoma.</instruction>
